description: Alien tourists visit Earth, with one adopting the role of a scarecrow, complete with being impaled on a stake in a field. Another alien visitor captures the bizarre scene with a camera, documenting their unusual interaction with human rural culture. A landed flying saucer sits nearby, highlighting the otherworldly origin of these strange activities. This surreal tableau plays on expectations, presenting invasion not as conquest, but as absurd cultural mimicry and photography.
